WEBVTT

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:05.280
It's really easy to go down those rabbit holes. What I've found works best for me and

00:00:07.280 --> 00:00:13.040
my team members that I've had do things is make sure that you are constantly working with

00:00:13.040 --> 00:00:18.559
business so that you're not going too far down a rabbit hole that they're like, I don't care about

00:00:18.559 --> 00:00:25.760
that. That doesn't affect me at all. Where if I can get the business partners feeling like

00:00:26.400 --> 00:00:31.440
it's their project and they're right beside you like helping through it,

00:00:32.639 --> 00:00:39.439
that decreases the rabbit holes. It's still easy, but I think we all have a tendency to be like,

00:00:39.439 --> 00:00:44.320
well, that's an interesting problem. Let's go look at it. But if you have that consistent

00:00:45.040 --> 00:00:50.480
relationship with the business person where you are truly working together and it's not just,

00:00:51.439 --> 00:00:54.799
okay, data scientist, go do your thing and then come back when you're done.

00:00:55.360 --> 00:01:01.119
That's when I think the rabbit hole problem gets bad. And there's a tendency for,

00:01:02.080 --> 00:01:08.800
I think both sides to be like, well, I'm busy in the business. So you just come back to me later.

00:01:08.800 --> 00:01:14.480
And that as the data scientist, I think you just cannot, you can't go for that.

00:01:14.480 --> 00:01:18.959
Like I require if I'm doing work with you or for you, you have to be my partner.

00:01:20.639 --> 00:01:26.480
Otherwise it's not going to succeed. I don't know if that helps you,

00:01:30.160 --> 00:01:34.320
but I have noticed people don't spend enough time creating that relationship

00:01:34.320 --> 00:01:35.839
and enforcing that relationship.

